ve years. Oil remains the biggest swing factor for headline inflation and for input costs at transport-, logistics-, and manufacturing-exposed borrowers."},{"tag":"Labor","text":"Payrolls added +57K in the latest report (+111K 3-month average), with unemployment at 4.2%. Hiring momentum is the leading read on demand durability for growth-oriented credits."},{"tag":"Inflation","text":"Headline CPI is running 3.5% YoY (-0.7pt vs the prior reading); core CPI 2.6%; core PCE \u2014 the Fed's target metric \u2014 3.4%. The gap between headline volatility (energy) and sticky core is the key tension for the rate path."},{"tag":"Policy","text":"The Fed funds target stands at 3.50\u20133.75%, with the 10Y\u20132Y curve at +37bp (normal upward slope). Base-rate assumptions in every floating-rate underwriting case key off this."},{"tag":"Credit","text":"HY OAS is 269bp \u2014 tighter than 92% of the past five years; IG OAS 78bp. Spread levels this stretched relative to history are the cleanest single gauge of how much credit risk is being paid for."},{"tag":"Growth","text":"Real GDP grew 2.1% (QoQ SAAR) in the most recent quarter and the Atlanta Fed's GDPNow is tracking +1.7% for the current quarter. Below-trend-but-positive growth remains the base case supporting growth-oriented over distressed positioning."},{"tag":"Consumer & Housing","text":"UMich consumer sentiment is 44.8, lower than 100% of the past five years; housing starts are 1.43M SAAR against a 6.55% 30Y mortgage rate. The consumer and housing complex is the most rate-sensitive part of the demand picture."}]},"themeCards":[{"title":"Energy shock / supply disruption","value":"Acute","dir":"up","statusLine":"Brent +$5.93 to $81.62 amid Iran tensions and Strait of Hormuz risk; <cite index=\"2-1\">ECB responds with hike driven by surging energy costs and inflation shock</cite>.","relevance":"High-cost refinancing into FY27-28 for energy-heavy, rate-sensitive credit; downstream leverage stress in petrochemicals, transportation, utilities. Spreads may gap on geopolitical escalation."},{"title":"Labor market cooling / wage growth deceleration","value":"Elevated","dir":"down","statusLine":"June payrolls +57K well below consensus; claims down but unemployment sticky at 4.2%. AHE growth modest at +3.52% YoY.","relevance":"Special situations investors should monitor refinancing risk for consumer-dependent sectors and watch for negative earnings guidance in Q2 earnings. Late-cycle dynamics favor credit picks with pricing power over commodity-exposed names."},{"title":"Sticky core inflation + rate hold bias","value":"Elevated","dir":"flat","statusLine":"Core CPI 2.57%, PCE core 3.41%, PPI 5.51% all elevated; 10y yields +22 bps WoW to 4.60%; ECB holding near-term despite energy shock.","relevance":"Curve inversion (10y-2y 37 bps) discounts limited duration relief. Higher refinancing costs for issuers with 2026-27 maturities; credit spreads may remain range-bound unless inflation clearly breaks lower or growth collapses suddenly."},{"title":"Private credit leverage & illiquidity tension","value":"Emerging","dir":"up","statusLine":"<cite index=\"35-21,35-22\">Private credit crisis not inevitable, but combination of leverage and illiquidity rarely ends well</cite>. <cite index=\"40-3\">Lower-quality issuers and leveraged private credit borrowers showing pressure</cite>.","relevance":"Key risk for special situations: stressed LBO refinancing in 2026-27, CLO defaults, and mark-to-market pressure if spreads widen sharply. Watch for fund gates and secondaries dislocations."},{"title":"Divergence in credit quality","value":"Elevated","dir":"flat","statusLine":"<cite index=\"39-1,39-2\">Loan performance uneven; some forecasters expect defaults to moderate while others warn of sectoral upticks</cite>. IG fundamentals strong, but HY dispersion widening.","relevance":"Bottom-up security selection critical; avoid broad index risk. Opportunities exist in higher-rated issuers with resilient EBITDA; distr